.TH "snd_hda_gen_add_kctl" 9 "snd_hda_gen_add_kctl" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
snd_hda_gen_add_kctl \- Add a new kctl_new struct from the template
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct snd_kcontrol_new *" snd_hda_gen_add_kctl
.BI "(struct hda_gen_spec *spec "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "const struct snd_kcontrol_new *temp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "spec" 12
hda_gen_spec object
.IP "name" 12
name string to override the template, NULL if unchanged
.IP "temp" 12
template for the new kctl
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Add a new kctl (actually snd_kcontrol_new to be instantiated later)
element based on the given snd_kcontrol_new template \fItemp\fP and the
name string \fIname\fP to the list in \fIspec\fP.
Returns the newly created object or NULL as error.
